children.subject: Discussion waiting list should be more important. You can only enroll in the lecture once your section has space.
Is there anyway to increase odds of getting off the waitlist? Also I noticed discussion sections all have less than 12 for each wait list total, but I'm number 16?

I believe CalCentral has a bug to show your actual waiting list position of sections. (I am not completely sure tho)  I think 16 is your lecture waiting list position. If you remembered how many people were on the section waiting list when you added that section, you can check out other sections to see if there is a section that has fewer people on the waiting list now. If so, it might help you to switch discussions.
CalCentral, like Telebears before it, only displays your position on the waiting list for the class, and does not break it down by section, yes.
I'm noticing there are two sections with available seats but have a waitlist total of 3+. Does this mean someone can directly enroll, or get added to the waitlist?
So I presume there's no way to know which section the waitlist has gone down for except to manually check it everyday?
Currently 16th on the lecture waitlist, but I'm enrolled in a discussion section. Which one's more important?
